HEADWORD: compact disk player
<hw>com"pact disk` play"er</hw></mhw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧m"p⟦acr⟧kt
d⟦icr⟧sk` pl⟦amac⟧"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>an electronic
device containing a laser, used to read or play back the data on a
compact disk. The term is usually used for the type of device used to
play music recordings. That used for data storage in computer
applications is usually called a <contr>CD drive</contr>. Called also
<altname>CD player</altname> and informally,
<altname>CD</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> CD player.</syn>⟦br⟧
